 © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Philip de Soligny was born in 1064, in Umberleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Soligny, was 27 and his mother, Baroness Alice of Umberleigh, was 23. He married Hawis de Vernon in 1095, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1114, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1064–1114":"1064–1114","0950–Male":"0950–Surnud","1068–1145":"1068–1145","1097–1157":"1097–1157","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1038–Male":"1038–Surnud","1042–Female":"1042–Surnud","0950":"0950","1038":"1038","1114":"1114","1157":"1157","1145":"1145","1068":"1068","1100":"1100","1064":"1064","1097":"1097","1042":"1042","1095":"1095","about 1100":"umbes 1100","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Umberleigh, Devonshire, England":"Umberleigh, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1064–1114":"1064–1114","0950–Male":"0950–Kuollut","1068–1145"